author: COMSOL
description:
Interfacial failure or delamination in a composite material is a common phenomenon. This can be simulated using Cohesive Zone Model (CZM).

This example shows the implementation of a CZM with a bilinear traction-separation law in a layered shell. It is used to predict the mixed-mode softening onset and delamination propagation.
label: progressive_delamination_in_a_laminated_shell.mph
